          "text": "The board of directors of an irrigation district may withdraw from any moneys deposited on behalf of the district an amount designated by the board and deposit it in an account with any insured institution, as defined in ORS 706.008, that is approved by the board to be maintained in the name of the district for the purposes set forth in subsection",
          "subsections": []
        },
        {
          "label": "(2)",
          "token": "2",
          "kind": "numeric",
          "text": "of this section. The account established under this section shall be used for the payment of any claims arising out of labor and emergency expenses incurred by the district during any month. Moneys may be withdrawn from the account by:",
          "subsections": [
            {
              "label": "(a)",
              "token": "a",
              "kind": "alpha_lower",
              "text": "Check or draft signed by at least two individuals authorized to do so by the board of directors; or",
              "subsections": []
            },
            {
